<!-- SECTION 2: Core Capabilities -->
<h2>Essential Workforce Management Features</h2>
<div class="citable-summary">
<strong>WorkMax unifies core functions including time tracking, scheduling, project management, and payroll integration‚Äîall designed to eliminate manual processes, improve accuracy, and give construction managers complete control of their labor operations.</strong>
</div>

<p><strong>Time and Attendance Tracking</strong> captures accurate clock-in and clock-out data through mobile apps with GPS location verification. Geofencing prevents employees from clocking in away from jobsites, while facial recognition eliminates buddy punching. Digital timesheets create audit trails satisfying OSHA and federal compliance requirements. Offline functionality ensures crews log hours even without connectivity‚Äîdata syncs automatically when connection returns.</p>

<p><strong>Project Coordination and Real-Time Visibility</strong> provides visibility into workforce availability, utilization, and task progress across multiple projects. This <strong>field labor management system</strong> helps managers track which workers are allocated to which projects and understand capacity across your operation. Supervisors gain visibility into crew status and task assignments, enabling informed decisions about resource allocation.</p>

<p><strong>Project-Integrated Data Management</strong> connects workforce information with project details, enabling better planning and progress tracking. Track labor hours by project, task, and cost code. Monitor actual labor against estimates in real-time. Compare project budgets to actual labor spend. This project-level integration transforms time data into actionable business intelligence.</p>

<p><strong>Payroll and Compliance Automation</strong> simplifies complex payroll scenarios construction requires. Handle overtime rules, differential pay rates, union certifications, prevailing wage compliance per U.S. Department of Labor (DOL) requirements, and multi-state labor law requirements automatically. <strong>Seamless integration with accounting software</strong> eliminates manual data entry and payroll errors. Digital records create compliance documentation satisfying state, federal, and union regulations.</p>

