<div class="faq-section">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-question">What is construction workforce management software?</div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
        <strong>Construction workforce management (WFM) software is a digital platform that helps construction managers organize, track, and manage their workforce across multiple jobsites.</strong> It combines time tracking, scheduling, project management, payroll, and compliance features into one integrated system. WFM software automates administrative tasks, provides real-time labor visibility, and helps construction companies control costs while ensuring compliance and safety. Unlike basic time tracking apps, comprehensive workforce optimization platforms connect labor data to project information for complete workforce visibility and decision-making capability.
    </div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-question">How does workforce management software help control construction labor costs?</div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
        <strong>WorkMax controls labor costs through accurate time tracking, real-time budget monitoring, and intelligent labor forecasting that prevents overstaffing and overtime waste.</strong> GPS and geofencing prevent buddy punching and off-site hours. Real-time dashboards show labor spending against project budgets immediately, enabling managers to adjust before costs spiral. Analytics reveal productivity trends and labor inefficiencies. Accurate job costing shows true labor expenses per project, improving future bid accuracy and competitiveness.
    </div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-question">Can workforce management software handle union and prevailing wage compliance?</div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
        <strong>Yes‚ÄîWorkMax automatically handles complex payroll scenarios including union certifications, DOL prevailing wage compliance, overtime rules, differential pay, and multi-state labor law requirements.</strong> The platform tracks employee certifications and training requirements, automatically flagging expired credentials per OSHA standards. Digital records create compliance documentation satisfying state, federal, and union regulations. Prevailing wage rates are applied correctly per project and location, ensuring compliance and accurate billing to clients.
    </div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-question">What integration capabilities does construction workforce management software provide?</div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
        <strong>WorkMax integrates with 100+ accounting, payroll, HR, and project management systems including QuickBooks, Sage, ADP, and major construction platforms.</strong> Labor data syncs automatically with accounting software for accurate financial reporting. Payroll systems receive verified timesheet data instantly. Project management systems gain real-time labor information for accurate forecasting. HR systems pull workforce data for comprehensive employee records. This integrated ERP approach eliminates manual data entry and ensures data consistency across your entire business.
    </div>
